# TypeScript backend quality

- Prefer explicit types on public APIs; avoid `any`; use generics on `getRequest<T>()` / guards.
- Functions: one clear responsibility; extract helpers when nesting exceeds two levels.
- Dependencies: constructor injection only; avoid service locators and hidden singletons.
- Config: use `ConfigService` for secrets and TTLs — not raw `process.env` in hot paths (except bootstrap).
- Match existing naming (`camelCase` TS, Drizzle schema casing conventions).
